<section xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
    <title>Specifying high level responsibilities around services domains</title>
    <para>
        The architect may require to obtain a deeper understanding of the high level responsibilities which need to be addressed around
        the services which the client aims to deploy within the architecture. For example, it may be relevant for the architect to understand
        that responsibilities around a rock concert include the ability to project images into the hall, that around the catering services one
        must be able to prepare snacks for the attendents, that the snacks, crockery, glasses and drinks need to be stored.
    </para>
</section>
    